how they died, their level, just making sure they knew I was still coming. So here's the kicker - I get to Blackburrow, and I ask them some other non-essential question, and I get "oh some other cleric just rezzed us."<BR>I was nice enough to agree to run almost 6 zones, and keep in touch to let them know I was coming, but they werent nice enough to wait for me - making me run 3 zones for nothing?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vamenea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This is slight off topic but my worst res experince was on a raid..<P>I got killed, ressed back in mid battle and gained low health aggro straight away and got killed again.<P>Got ressed in again mid battle and gained low health aggro straight away and got killed again.<P>So thats three deaths, for those that are not counting even though we where low numbers for this raid I refused to click on the yes button to be ressed back in till there where no mobs in camp<P><BR>Vamnea Deryther<BR>Templar of Innoruuk</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ozymandia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This all worked out in the end but made me feel pretty crappy for a while ..<P>In Sol B.  My 57 warrior friend and I (newly dinged 40) were killing kobolds and bats, trying to get me a level buffer.<P>I'm at the zone-in while he runs around smiting dogs mightily.  I get a tell:<P>"Hi, could you please spare a revive at the pool room?"<P>I say I'd be happy to revive, but I'm not familiar with the zone ~ if he'd drag it to me, I'd be happy to.<P>He pulls the body to me, and I take a look.  Now, I'd seen this dead person about 15 minutes before this do /ooc Sorry!!  right before a train of kobolds smashed me flat.  I'd seen an iksar monk run by right before; this corpse was an iksar monk, same name.  I said:<P>/say "Hmm this is the guy who trained me earlier."<P>Nevertheless, being the nice loving cleric that I am, I sent a tell to the dead person and said "Revive incoming," and revived him, since revive is what was asked for.  The person standing there who had brought the body said:<P>"Revive?  Can't you rez?"<P>I said:<P>"Oh, you said revive.  Ok, meming rez, one sec."<P>Sat down to mem my rez, when I hear the revived monk say "REVIVE?"<P>So for the next hour I hear in /ooc all about how I'm a crappy cleric who would only revive someone because I thought they had trained me, and that I had allegedly told the first guy that a revive was all I would give because I was trained.  I was slightly miffed.  Never mind that I had TOLD him it was a revive that was incoming, and that he had clicked "Yes" to a revive; he insisted I had maliciously cost him 2 bubs of exp at level 54.<P>However, after sending a /tell finally to the revived monk, we worked out that his guildmate had asked for the wrong spell unintentionally, and that he had misunderstood me.  I'm not sure how, but he did.  Anyway, that's my worst rez story, and I felt like crap for quite a while that night.  Ah well, such is my life /grin<P>Ozymandia</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Amojoman</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My worst res request happened when I zoned into Feerrott to pick up my roommate's enchanter to get him to help with the 9th ring quest in Great Divide.  <P>Had just ported into Feerrott when I got a request for help.  I responded that I wasn't able to help.  Since my roommate was already at the Feerrott druid ring, it took less than 30 seconds to pick him up and port back to Great Divide.  Upon zoning back into Great Divide, I get a tell from the same guy saying, "Well you're not in the same zone anymore."  followed immediately with "THANKS FOR THE HELP A**" (astericks weren't there in the tell).  I got another nasty tell from him which involved 4 letter words.  Out of anger I told him to piss off and then put him on /ignore.  <P>The next day I happened to be ressing one of his guild officer's group in Eastern Wastes and talked to him about the conversation I had with the guy.  The guy was either /guildremoved or left on his own, but a week later when I ran into the guy again, he was guildless.<P>My biggest pet peeve of all was being told by my group, "We don't want your res because you're only 54.  We're going to wait until a 56+ Cleric zones in"  I left the group, ressed myself and haven't returned to the zone as of yet.  Currently 57 and have had the pleasure of turning down res requests from 3 of the 5 that were in that group.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Amojoman Woundhealer<BR>56th Templar, serving the healing needs of <A HREF="http://pub22.ezboard.com/bsentinelsofchaos" TARGET=_blank>Sentinels of Chaos</A><BR>"Be careful of the words you speak. Make them soft and sweet. You never know from day to day, which ones you'll have to eat."--Author unknown"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gabrianna</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've posted this on another board but I'll go ahead and post it here too.<P>My worst res request was when I dinged 29.  It had taken me 45 minutes to get a port out of Ill Omen simply because my cleric is a high elf and even sow'd runs very slowly.  Any agro from the drachnids and she'd be toast.<P>Anyway I finally got a port and an instant before LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... I receive a tell something like "could you res me pls".  I couldn't even get a reply in before zoning so as soon as I zoned, I replied and our conversation went something like this:<P>Me:  I'm sorry, I was being ported out when I received your message.<BR>Him: I don't know why you play a cleric, you suck!<BR>Me:  Excuse me?  I haven't even bought the spell yet you jerk.<BR>Him:  Whatever<BR>/ignore him<P>The attitude of some people boggles the mind.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerycho</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My most amusing rez experience came just the other day. I'm running through NFreeport to the bank to, well, bank. Then I'm heading to SolB for some adventuring. I'm bound in Kael for a variety of reasons and I'm not changing the bind point anytime soon.<P>Anyway, I get a tell from someone asking if I'll come out to OoT adn rez them. I respond that I'm banking and running to SolB and that I don't want to go spend an hour riding the boat, so no thanks.<P>I get a tell back saying "I'll pay you 20p."<P>I told the guild about it and we had a good long laugh.<P>My response was basically "um, in SolB I will make 100p in an hour, not to mention a good amount of xp. You're asking me to give that up for the joy of being bored on a boat for an hour and 20p? don't think so  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">"<P>I then got spammed with a few well choosen words about how I was a lousy cleric.<P>And people wonder why clerics get a bad attitude :/</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just got the ability to rez but my overall worst experience was in KC.<P>They dragged the body to the Safe Side (SS) and then someone takes the train to that side.  I think I spent an hour and half rezzing with bard song and a necro feeding me.  Hehe I didn't even request donations - think we did 14 rezzes that night.<P>/hugs<BR>Torriana<BR>Cleric<BR>Shelsea<BR>Druid<P>Brell Serilis</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chronomis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I know it's a rant board, but I saw this topic and I couldn't resist the urge to inject a little reason.  I play a non-cleric most of the time, so my worse rez experience is probably the single most common bad rez experience of them all.  Quite simply, I died and couldn't get a rez.  Something to consider when you consider what a bad rez experience is.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kimbera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Chronomis:<BR><B>I know it's a rant board, but I saw this topic and I couldn't resist the urge to inject a little reason.  I play a non-cleric most of the time, so my worse rez experience is probably the single most common bad rez experience of them all.  Quite simply, I died and couldn't get a rez.  Something to consider when you consider what a bad rez experience is.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I understand what you're saying, since I play non-cleric PCs as well.  My characters die without getting resurrected more often than I want to admit.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>But... losing some experience and time because I died is NOWHERE near as bad as having my time wasted by "people" (term is used advisedly) who are absolutely convinced that their time is more valuable than mine, harrass me if I do not subject myself to their every whim, and do not even express appreciation if I do help them.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chronomis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/cackle<P>My main is a druid.  Do you even want to think about the tells for SoW, ports, buffs, items, and powerleveling, many of them quite rude, that I receive every day?  I know very well what it means to have unreasonable demands made on your time by inconsiderate people who are too lazy to get to a druid ring, or aren't ready for a port when you get there.  <P>Powerleveling?  Why sure, I have a spare week with nothing better to do than powerlevel you.  What else could I possibly be doing?  Oh, yes.  I could be waiting for that person I agreed to port fifteen mintues ago to finish his banking four zones away so I can port him!  <P>FYI:  I don't charge for ports, but sometimes I do take people up on their offer if they're shouting a price to the zone.  Not sure where people come up with this idea that druids have lots of items to hand out.  I may not have the cost of peridots to bear, but I also almost never have more than 500pp to my name and quite mediocre gear.<P> - Chronomis<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sighs, think this whole weekend should count for worst rez experiences.  In two days, 58 rezzes and no one compensates sigh.  3 failed raids and 2 stupid group leaders.  Rezzed people wandering around and training the clerics rezzing.<P>/hugs</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pastor Skellbane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">EEPS! <P>Along with your other post Shelsea not a good weekend then  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>*hugs*</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">chukoliang</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmmm, I don't know if it seems horrible to you but I will tell you what I feel was the personal worst rez experience, I had.<P>I have had the tells from across the world. I have had people begging for rez's. I have even had people telling me I was a jerk and more,because I didn't travel 6 zones to rez some total stranger. I have had totally twinked out guys with super items who don't give me a dime for the rez. And of course what I usually get is a thank you , I don't require a donation,but when your as poor as I am, it sure helps. Even a buff is good  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>But my worst experience was when I had just died in burning woods hunting wasps with a drui