ay no to ppl, and after 5 minutes of me saying I couldnt really do it, I buckled to the harrassment and my cleric nature took over. I almost never charge for ressing. However I like ppl to offer (so I can say no anyway). If however I run many zones I will never turn down a donation.<P>So Im offered 100pp which I feel is more a token payment as I say its not the money its the principal of the thing.<P>I run to CT, no sow or jboots, took me about 20 or 30 mins if I remember right and when I arrive it turns out they need a CR too. So I CR their corpses from the underground part solo, place with all the walk ways, and res not 1 but 3 of them, by now my time is getting well over an hour wasted. They all say how great I am etc, but once ressed they just went silent and all 3 of them logged, not even 1cp offered. I was quite peturbed that someone could be so dishonest and abuse someones kind nature like that, promising donations but making non. <P>However I wasnt that kind, they conned the wrong guy, being a guildleader I could ensure they never got a res from my guild ever again  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif">and a few of our alliances heard about them too  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"> What goes around comes around......<P>Muahahaha<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bolgor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Refferring to the person who said they mostly play a non-cleric and sometimes go without any res... I cannot recall a single time when I died with one of my non-cleric alts and looked for a res. With my non-cleric alts I eat xp deaths for breakfast. I know what its like to be dragged out of a group and across 3 zones to do a res, and I never want to put anyone thru that. XP can be hunted if lost. An hour of running zoning and ressing can never be returned.<P>Personally as much as i hate doing those out of the way resses, I try to do them as often 